**Pattern rotation math**: The 90-degree clockwise Y-axis rotation maps `old[z][x]` → `new[old_x][maxZ - old_z]`. This is the standard 2D rotation matrix applied per-layer, preserving Y stacking. Four rotations return to identity — verified by the round-trip test.

